orized","issuingAuthorityTitle":"Certificate authority","certId":60005863484,"certOwnTypeTitle":"Certificate type:","issuingAuthority":"Other","certValidPeriod":"05/17/2023 - 05/17/2028","aiSummary":["<b>Applicable industries:</b> Electronic and electrical products","<b>Applicable regions:</b> The European Union and major global markets","<b>Certification standards:</b> Restricting the content of harmful substances such as lead, mercury, and cadmium","<b>Advantages:</b> Complies with environmental protection requirements, enhancing international market access and competitiveness."],"certName":"RoHS","certValidPeriodTitle":"Validity period","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/Hdcdda68a5c974643bba82b99a60a9907G.png","imageList":["https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/Heba395ea0877430ea8f1b638ae5ec89d2.png"],"introduction":"The Restriction of Hazardous Substances (RoHS) Directive is a regulation established by the European Union to limit the use of specific hazardous substances in electrical and electronic equipment. Managed by the European Commission, the directive reduces environmental and health risks by restricting substances such as lead, mercury and cadmium, ensuring safer production and disposal methods for technology products.  \n\nRoHS compliance is a legal requirement for electronic products sold within the EU, covering items ranging from household appliances to industrial equipment. Products meeting this standard demonstrate adherence to stringent safety protocols, not only minimising legal barriers in cross-border trade but also proving reliability to buyers prioritising supply chain sustainability and regulatory compliance."},{"summary":{"certificationStandard":"Restricting the content of harmful substances such as lead, mercury, and cadmium","sellingPoint":"RoHS compliant","certificateAdvantages":"Complies with environmental protection requirements, enhancing international market access and competitiveness.","applicableIndustry":"Electronic and electrical products