","name":"CE","description":"Complies with EU standards","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/Hdbbb6a106e8d4515be692063768d8fd4J.png","type":"CE","items":[{"summary":{"certificationStandard":"The EU legal regulations on safety, health, and environmental requirements, such as 2014/35/EU, 2014/30/EU, and 2014/53/EU, etc.","sellingPoint":"Complies with EU standards","certificateAdvantages":"The \"passport\" for products entering the markets of EU countries and EFTA countries","applicableIndustry":"All products exported to the European Union","applicableRegions":"European Economic Area"},"certType":"PRODUCT","certOwnType":"Manufacturer-authorized","issuingAuthorityTitle":"Certificate authority","certId":60005834699,"certOwnTypeTitle":"Certificate type:","issuingAuthority":"Other","certValidPeriod":"02/26/2025 - 02/26/2030","aiSummary":["<b>Applicable industries:</b> All products exported to the European Union","<b>Applicable regions:</b> European Economic Area","<b>Certification standards:</b> The EU legal regulations on safety, health, and environmental requirements, such as 2014/35/EU, 2014/30/EU, and 2014/53/EU, etc.","<b>Advantages:</b> The \"passport\" for products entering the markets of EU countries and EFTA countries"],"certName":"CE","certValidPeriodTitle":"Validity period","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/Hdbbb6a106e8d4515be692063768d8fd4J.png","imageList":["https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/H79498017fbfc4ffbb5f47f6d93550a2dI.png"],"introduction":"The CE (Conformité Européenne) marking is a European Union certification that verifies a product's compliance with core health, safety and environmental protection standards required for sale in the European Economic Area. As a mandatory certification for product categories including electronics, machinery and medical devices entering EU markets, this designation confirms legal market access across 31 European countries. It remains critical for importers fulfilling EU regulatory obligations. Suppliers holding this certification demonstrate commitment to product quality and responsible manufacturing practices aligning with European sustainability objectives."}]},{"certType":"INSPECTION_REPORT","name":"EN 62368","description":"IEC 62368-1 compliant","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/H193254a0dfa94861b01d46e92f713258D.png","type":"EN 62368","items":[{"summary":{"certificationStandard":"EN IEC 62368 is the product safety standard for audio, video, information technology, and communication technology equipment.","sellingPoint":"IEC 62368-1 compliant","certificateAdvantages":"Complies with electrical safety and fire protection requirements, reducing the risk of electric shock and fire.","applicableIndustry":"Audio, video, and information technology equipment","applicableRegions":"European Union"},"certType":"INSPECTION_REPORT","certOwnType":"Manufacturer-authorized","issuingAuthorityTitle":"Certificate authority","certId":60005857100,"certOwnTypeTitle":"Certificate type:","issuingAuthority":"Other","certValidPeriod":"02/26/2025 - 11/11/2026","aiSummary":["<b>Applicable industries:</b> Audio, video, and information technology equipment","<b>Applicable regions:</b> European Union","<b>Certification standards:</b> EN IEC 62368 is the product safety standard for audio, video, information technology, and communication technology equipment.","<b>Advantages:</b> Complies with electrical safety and fire protection requirements, reducing the risk of electric shock and fire."],"certName":"EN 62368","certValidPeriodTitle":"Validity period","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/H193254a0dfa94861b01d46e92f713258D.png","imageList":["https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/H2febbfc76f7b4551b01175110008688aw.png"],"introduction":"EN 62368-1 is a harmonised safety standard established by the European Committee for Electrotechnical Standardisation (CENELEC) and enforced under the EU CE Marking Directives. It defines hazard-based safety requirements for audio/video equipment, information technology, and communication technology devices, prioritising risk prevention through design and testing protocols. \n\nThis standard holds legal force for electronic products sold within the European Economic Area (EEA), covering power supply units, IT hardware, and consumer electronics. Compliance certification ensures adherence to EU safety regulations, mitigates buyer liability risks, confirms market access eligibility across the EEA, enhances product reliability, and strengthens buyer confidence."}]},{"certType":"INSPECTION_REPORT","name":"EN 301 489","description":"EMC Ready","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/H9724c58a6db14e478bb6c616675972ccP.png","type":"EN 301 489","items":[{"summary":{"certificationStandard":"Radio frequency electromagnetic compatibility (EMC) standards developed by the European Telecommunications Standards Institute (ETSI)","sellingPoint":"EMC Ready","certificateAdvantages":"Obtaining this certification demonstrates that the product complies with regional safety standards, reduces legal risks for buyers, and ensures compatibility with other CE-certified equipment, which is crucial for the product's smooth entry into the market.","applicableIndustry":"Wireless communication equipment","applicableRegions":"Europe"},"certType":"INSPECTION_REPORT","certOwnType":"Manufacturer-authorized","issuingAuthorityTitle":"Certificate authority","certId":60005857098,"certOwnTypeTitle":"Certificate type:","issuingAuthority":"Other","certValidPeriod":"02/26/2025 - 11/11/2026","aiSummary":["<b>Applicable industries:</b> Wireless communication equipment","<b>Applicable regions:</b> Europe","<b>Certification standards:</b> Radio frequency electromagnetic compatibility (EMC) standards developed by the European Telecommunications Standards Institute (ETSI)","<b>Advantages:</b> Obtaining this certification demonstrates that the product complies with regional safety standards, reduces legal risks for buyers, and ensures compatibility with other CE-certified equipment, which is crucial for the product's smooth entry into the market."],"certName":"EN 301 489","certValidPeriodTitle":"Validity period","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/H9724c58a6db14e478bb6c616675972ccP.png","imageList":["https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/H743dea6801bc47a2af536b58c8099d8dd.png"],"introduction":"The EN 301 489 standard, developed by the European Telecommunications Standards Institute (ETSI) and mandated under EU directives, ensures the electromagnetic compatibility (EMC) of radio equipment. It specifies requirements to minimise electromagnetic interference between devices, ensuring reliable operation in shared environments and maintaining the stable performance of communication and electronic systems. \n\nProducts with radio functionalities, such as Wi-Fi routers and IoT devices, sold in the EU must comply with the EN 301 489 standard to meet the Radio Equipment Directive (RED) requirements. Achieving this certification demonstrates adherence to regional safety regulations, reduces legal risks for buyers, and ensures compatibility with other CE-marked devices—essential for seamless market access and distribution."}]},{"certType":"INSPECTION_REPORT","name":"ETSI EN 300 328","description":"Bluetooth/WiFi Ready","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/Ha23381fb66c84727912f8108d66979a5B.png","type":"ETSI EN 300 328","items":[{"summary":{"certificationStandard":"Requirements and testing methods for wireless devices operating in the 2.4 GHz frequency band regarding radio frequency and electromagnetic compatibility","sellingPoint":"Bluetooth/WiFi Ready","certificateAdvantages":"Complies with EU radio spectrum compliance requirements, ensuring the normal operation of devices in the 2.4 GHz band.","applicableIndustry":"Wireless communication equipment","applicableRegions":"Europe"},"certType":"INSPECTION_REPORT","certOwnType":"Manufacturer-authorized","issuingAuthorityTitle":"Certificate authority","certId":60005869014,"certOwnTypeTitle":"Certificate type:","issuingAuthority":"Other","certValidPeriod":"02/26/2025 - 11/11/2026","aiSummary":["<b>Applicable industries:</b> Wireless communication equipment","<b>Applicable regions:</b> Europe","<b>Certification standards:</b> Requirements and testing methods for wireless devices operating in the 2.4 GHz frequency band regarding radio frequency and electromagnetic compatibility","<b>Advantages:</b> Complies with EU radio spectrum compliance requirements, ensuring the normal operation of devices in the 2.4 GHz band."],"certName":"ETSI EN 300 328","certValidPeriodTitle":"Validity period","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/Ha23381fb66c84727912f8108d66979a5B.png","imageList":["https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/H3dc182a55753487d9ac39ba9730bdf7f9.png"],"introduction":"ETSI EN 300 328 is a harmonised European standard established by the European Telecommunications Standards Institute (ETSI) to regulate the operation of broadband transmission systems in the 2.4 GHz ISM band. This standard ensures wireless devices such as Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and Zigbee comply with the technical requirements for spectrum efficiency, coexistence, and interference avoidance within the European Economic Area (EEA).  \n\nUnder the EU Radio Equipment Directive (RED 2014/53/EU), compliance with this standard is a mandatory requirement for products to obtain market access in Europe. It applies to manufacturers and importers of 2.4 GHz wireless products, including IoT devices and industrial equipment. Certification demonstrates that a product’s radio frequency performance meets EEA regulatory requirements, reduces legal risks in cross-border trade, and enhances buyer confidence."}]},{"certType":"INSPECTION_REPORT","name":"EN 50663","description":"SAR Safety Compliant","iconUrl":"https://sc04.alicdn.com/kf/H193254a0dfa94861b01d46e92f713258D.png","type":"EN 50663","items":[{"summary":{"certificationStandard":"General evaluation criteria for low-voltage electronic and electrical equipment regarding limits on human exposure to electromagne